{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:33:18.504464+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have all the information needed. Here's the full summary.\n\n---\n\n## npm Scripts\n\nThis repository has scripts defined in **two places**, reflecting its nature as a CRA (Create React App) template:\n\n### Root `package.json` (template packaging & deployment)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `start` | `react-scripts start` | Start the dev server |\n| `build` | `react-scripts build` | Create a production build |\n| `test` | `react-scripts test` | Run the test suite |\n| `eject` | `react-scripts eject` | Eject from CRA |\n| `predeploy` | `npm run build` | Auto-runs before `deploy` |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d build` | Deploy the `build/` folder to GitHub Pages |\n| `clean-files` | `rm -rf ./template/public ./template/src` | Remove stale template sources |\n| `copy-files` | `cp -a ./src/. template/src && cp -a ./public/. template/public` | Copy current source into the template directory |\n| `prepublishOnly` | `npm run clean-files && npm run copy-files` | Prepares the template for `npm publish` |\n\n### `template.json` (scripts injected into user projects created from this template)\n\nIn addition to the standard CRA scripts above, the **template** provides two extra convenience scripts:\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `serve` | `serve -s build` | Serve the production build locally via [serve](https://www.npmjs.com/package/serve) |\n| `build-and-serve` | `npm run build && npm run serve` | Build a production bundle **and** serve it locally in one step |\n| `pull` | `git pull && npm i && npm start` | Pull latest code, install deps, and start dev server |\n\n---\n\n## Guidance for Testing a Production Build Locally Before Publishing/Deploying\n\nThe README's **\"To Deploy on GitHub Pages\"** section (step 3) documents this explicitly:\n\n1. **Temporarily set `homepage` to `\"/\"`** in `package.json`. (This avoids CRA trying to resolve absolute asset paths for a remote domain while you're testing locally.)\n2. **Install `serve` globally** if you haven't already:\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g serve\n   ```\n3. **Run the combined build-and-serve script:**\n   ```bash\n   npm run build-and-serve\n   ```\n   This produces a production-optimized `build/` directory and immediately serves it locally (typically at `http://localhost:3000`).\n\n4. **Once you've verified everything works**, set `homepage` back to your actual hosting domain (e.g., `https://your-github-username.github.io/your-repo-name`) and deploy:\n   ```bash\n   npm run deploy\n   ```\n\n> **Important note:** The `build-and-serve` and `serve` scripts are defined in `template.json` (i.e., they exist in **projects created from** this template), but they are **not** present in the root `package.json` of this repository itself. If you're working directly in this repo, you'd need to either add them manually or run the two steps separately:\n> ```bash\n> npm run build\n> npx serve -s build\n> ```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1366, "prompt_tokens": 9296, "total_tokens": 10662, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 639, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8832, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0004721696, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 8.96896e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00038248}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871584-d75PQTvCZ8h1fACQ27BA", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea437-d9b6-70a1-b384-d34c43b5e463-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": 